{"_type":"issue","id":"voice-assistant-1778121068071-15-075b24c1","title":"Voicemail detection + voicemail outcome","description":"## Parent\n\n#1 â€” PRD: AI-Powered Outbound Personal Calling Assistant\n\n## What to build\n\nHandle the voicemail path: Vapi detects the call went to voicemail â†’ agent leaves a message based on the CallPlan goal â†’ CallSession transitions to `voicemail` â†’ OutcomeExtractor runs â†’ user sees a \"Left voicemail\" Outcome.\n\nEnd-to-end: user's call goes to voicemail â†’ agent leaves a short, purposeful message (not a sales pitch) â†’ CallSession reaches `voicemail` state â†’ Outcome shows \"Left voicemail\" with the message content â†’ user can choose to retry.\n\n- `voicemail` webhook event from Vapi triggers `voicemail` state transition\n- VapiAdapter config includes a voicemail instruction: leave a brief message stating purpose and callback number (user's phone from CallPlan `allowed_to_share`)\n- OutcomeExtractor handles `voicemail` state: `outcome.status = \"voicemail\"`, `outcome.summary` = what was left\n- UI: CallSession page shows \"Left voicemail\" state with summary and a \"Retry call\" button\n- Voicemail message is logged in transcript\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] `voicemail` Vapi event transitions CallSession to `voicemail` state\n- [ ] VapiAdapter config includes voicemail message instructions\n- [ ] `ExtractOutcomeJob` is enqueued on `voicemail` state (same as `completed`)\n- [ ] Outcome for voicemail has `status: \"voicemail\"` and a summary of what was left\n- [ ] UI shows \"Left voicemail\" with summary and \"Retry call\" affordance\n- [ ] Voicemail message content appears in transcript\n- [ ] Test covers `voicemail` webhook â†’ state transition â†’ outcome shape\n\n## Blocked by\n\n- #8 â€” WebhookProcessor","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"Eric Dahl","created_at":"2026-05-07T02:30:47Z","updated_at":"2026-05-07T05:58:29Z","started_at":"2026-05-07T05:51:59Z","closed_at":"2026-05-07T05:58:29Z","close_reason":"Closed","external_ref":"https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/15","source_system":"github:https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/15:15","metadata":null,"labels":["ready-for-agent"],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"voice-assistant-1778121067954-14-fd85cbf4","title":"Escalation reply handler: resume or fallback on timeout","description":"## Parent\n\n#1 â€” PRD: AI-Powered Outbound Personal Calling Assistant\n\n## What to build\n\nHandle the two paths after an Escalation is created: (1) user replies in time â†’ agent resumes the call with the answer, (2) no reply within timeout â†’ agent falls back to the `CallPlan#fallback` instruction.\n\nEnd-to-end: user taps the reply URL from Pushover/SMS â†’ submits yes/no or freeform reply â†’ `Escalation#user_reply` saved â†’ Vapi is instructed to resume with the answer. If `EscalationTimeoutJob` fires first â†’ `Escalation#timed_out = true` â†’ Vapi is instructed to execute the fallback.\n\n- Reply endpoint (POST `/escalations/:id/reply`) â€” authenticated, token-protected link\n- Stores `user_reply` and `resolved_at` on the Escalation\n- Calls VapiAdapter to resume the call with the user's answer\n- `EscalationTimeoutJob` (GoodJob) enqueued at `notified_at + timeout` (configurable, default 45s)\n- On timeout: sets `timed_out = true`, calls VapiAdapter to execute `call_plan.fallback`\n- If user replies after timeout has already fired: reply is saved but no further Vapi call is made\n- CallSession transitions from `needs_user â†’ in_conversation` on resume, or to `completed` if fallback ends the call\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Reply URL is unique per Escalation and requires authentication or a signed token\n- [ ] Submitting a reply before timeout stores `user_reply`, sets `resolved_at`, and resumes the Vapi call\n- [ ] `EscalationTimeoutJob` fires at the configured timeout\n- [ ] On timeout: `timed_out = true`, Vapi executes `call_plan.fallback`\n- [ ] Late reply (after timeout) is stored but does not trigger a second Vapi resume\n- [ ] CallSession transitions correctly on resume (`needs_user â†’ in_conversation`)\n- [ ] Timeout duration is configurable via env/config (not hardcoded)\n- [ ] Tests cover: reply before timeout, timeout with no reply, late reply after timeout\n\n## Blocked by\n\n- #13 â€” EscalationNotifier","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"Eric Dahl","created_at":"2026-05-07T02:30:32Z","updated_at":"2026-05-07T05:51:21Z","started_at":"2026-05-07T05:41:45Z","closed_at":"2026-05-07T05:51:21Z","close_reason":"Closed","external_ref":"https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/14","source_system":"github:https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/14:14","metadata":null,"labels":["ready-for-agent"],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"voice-assistant-1778121067838-13-506f5b26","title":"EscalationNotifier: Pushover + SMS on needs_user","description":"## Parent\n\n#1 â€” PRD: AI-Powered Outbound Personal Calling Assistant\n\n## What to build\n\n`EscalationNotifier` fires when a `CallSession` enters `needs_user`. It simultaneously sends a Pushover notification and a Twilio SMS to the user with the blocking question and a reply URL. The Escalation record is created to track the reply window.\n\nEnd-to-end: Vapi sends `escalation.triggered` webhook with a blocking question â†’ WebhookProcessor creates an `Escalation` record and calls `EscalationNotifier` â†’ user receives both a Pushover push and an SMS within seconds â†’ both messages contain the question and a link/reply path.\n\nSchema (already defined in PRD):\n```\nescalations: id, call_session_id, question, notified_at,\n             user_reply, resolved_at, timed_out (bool)\n```\n\n- `EscalationNotifier.notify(escalation:, user:)` sends both channels simultaneously (not sequentially)\n- Pushover: title = \"Call on hold\", message = question + reply URL, high priority\n- SMS (Twilio): \"[Caller on hold] {question} â€” Reply here: {url}\"\n- Both fire even if one fails (rescue each independently, log errors)\n- `Escalation#notified_at` set after both are dispatched\n- Pushover API key and Twilio credentials from Rails credentials / env\n- Both services stubbed in tests\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] `EscalationNotifier` sends Pushover notification on escalation\n- [ ] `EscalationNotifier` sends Twilio SMS on escalation\n- [ ] Both are sent simultaneously, not sequentially\n- [ ] If one channel fails, the other still fires\n- [ ] `Escalation#notified_at` is set after dispatch\n- [ ] Pushover message includes the blocking question and reply URL\n- [ ] SMS includes the blocking question and reply URL\n- [ ] Tests stub both Pushover and Twilio â€” no real API calls\n\n## Blocked by\n\n- #8 â€” WebhookProcessor","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"Eric Dahl","created_at":"2026-05-07T02:30:16Z","updated_at":"2026-05-07T05:41:27Z","started_at":"2026-05-07T05:36:25Z","closed_at":"2026-05-07T05:41:27Z","close_reason":"Closed","external_ref":"https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/13","source_system":"github:https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/13:13","metadata":null,"labels":["ready-for-agent"],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"voice-assistant-1778121067721-12-82fae7e7","title":"Outcome display UI + Delegation history","description":"## Parent\n\n#1 â€” PRD: AI-Powered Outbound Personal Calling Assistant\n\n## What to build\n\nShow users the structured Outcome after a call completes, and a full Delegation history page showing all past calls and their results.\n\nEnd-to-end: user lands on a completed CallSession page and sees a clear summary, important details, follow-up flag, and full transcript. They can also visit a Delegation history page listing all past Delegations with outcomes at a glance.\n\n- CallSession show page: outcome summary card, important_details list, follow_up_needed banner (if true), confidence indicator, full transcript (collapsible)\n- Delegation index page: list of all user Delegations, each showing target name, date, outcome status, and one-line summary\n- Turbo Stream updates Outcome section when `ExtractOutcomeJob` completes (replaces \"Analysing callâ€¦\" placeholder)\n- `follow_up_needed: true` renders a prominent call-to-action (\"You may need to follow up\")\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Completed CallSession page shows summary, important_details, follow_up_needed, confidence, and transcript\n- [ ] While Outcome is being extracted, page shows \"Analysing callâ€¦\" placeholder\n- [ ] Turbo Stream replaces placeholder with Outcome when extraction completes\n- [ ] Delegation history page lists all Delegations for the current user, newest first\n- [ ] Each row shows: target name, date, outcome status badge, one-line summary\n- [ ] `follow_up_needed: true` renders a distinct banner on the CallSession page\n- [ ] `declined` outcome renders \"Business declined AI call\" (not \"completed\")\n\n## Blocked by\n\n- #11 â€” OutcomeExtractor","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"Eric Dahl","created_at":"2026-05-07T02:30:00Z","updated_at":"2026-05-07T05:36:07Z","started_at":"2026-05-07T05:31:35Z","closed_at":"2026-05-07T05:36:07Z","close_reason":"Closed","external_ref":"https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/12","source_system":"github:https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/12:12","metadata":null,"labels":["ready-for-agent"],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"voice-assistant-1778121067614-11-63386492","title":"OutcomeExtractor: transcript â†’ structured Outcome","description":"## Parent\n\n#1 â€” PRD: AI-Powered Outbound Personal Calling Assistant\n\n## What to build\n\n`OutcomeExtractor` takes a completed transcript and the originating `CallPlan` and produces a structured `Outcome` that is persisted to `CallSession#outcome`. It runs as a background job after a CallSession reaches `completed` or `voicemail`.\n\nEnd-to-end: Vapi sends `call.ended` â†’ WebhookProcessor transitions to `completed` â†’ `ExtractOutcomeJob` enqueued â†’ `OutcomeExtractor` calls an LLM with the transcript + CallPlan goal/questions â†’ structured Outcome written to the CallSession â†’ UI updates.\n\nOutcome shape:\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"completed\",\n  \"outcome\": \"Car is ready for pickup.\",\n  \"follow_up_needed\": false,\n  \"summary\": \"Bob's Auto said the Honda Odyssey is ready. Total is $284.17. Pickup before 5:30 PM.\",\n  \"important_details\": [\"Total: $284.17\", \"Pickup before 5:30 PM\", \"Bring card used for deposit\"],\n  \"confidence\": \"high\"\n}\n```\n\n- `OutcomeExtractor` service: takes `transcript` (string) + `call_plan` â†’ returns Outcome hash\n- LLM prompt uses CallPlan `goal` and `questions_to_ask` as extraction targets\n- `confidence` is `high | medium | low` based on how clearly the transcript answers the goal\n- `ExtractOutcomeJob` (GoodJob) enqueued by WebhookProcessor on `completed` or `voicemail`\n- LLM provider configurable via env (OpenAI by default)\n- Tested with fixture transcripts â€” no real LLM calls in tests\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] `OutcomeExtractor` returns a valid Outcome hash for a well-formed transcript\n- [ ] `questions_to_ask` answers are surfaced in `important_details`\n- [ ] `confidence` is set to `low` when the transcript does not clearly answer the goal\n- [ ] `follow_up_needed` is `true` when the Outcome is ambiguous or incomplete\n- [ ] `ExtractOutcomeJob` is enqueued by WebhookProcessor on `completed` and `voicemail`\n- [ ] Outcome is persisted to `CallSession#outcome` after extraction\n- [ ] Tests use fixture transcripts â€” no real LLM calls\n\n## Blocked by\n\n- #8 â€” WebhookProcessor","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"Eric Dahl","created_at":"2026-05-07T02:29:47Z","updated_at":"2026-05-07T05:26:56Z","started_at":"2026-05-07T05:22:30Z","closed_at":"2026-05-07T05:26:56Z","close_reason":"Closed","external_ref":"https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/11","source_system":"github:https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/11:11","metadata":null,"labels":["ready-for-agent"],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"voice-assistant-1778121067502-10-e3f2beaf","title":"Disclosure enforcement + declined outcome handling","description":"## Parent\n\n#1 â€” PRD: AI-Powered Outbound Personal Calling Assistant\n\n## What to build\n\nEnforce that every CallSession opens with the mandatory Disclosure statement, and handle the case where the business declines to continue after hearing it (ADR-0003).\n\nEnd-to-end: the VapiAdapter always injects the Disclosure instruction into every assistant config â€” there is no code path that omits it. When Vapi signals a `declined` event (business said no after disclosure), `WebhookProcessor` transitions the CallSession to `completed` and writes an Outcome with `status: \"declined\"`. The UI shows a clear \"Business declined AI call\" message.\n\n- Disclosure instruction is a constant injected by `VapiAdapter` â€” not user-configurable\n- `WebhookProcessor` handles a `call.declined` (or equivalent) Vapi event\n- On declined: CallSession â†’ `completed`, `outcome.status = \"declined\"`, `outcome.summary` = \"The business declined to continue after the AI disclosure.\"\n- `declined` is never retried with different framing (ADR-0003)\n- UI: CallSession page shows a distinct \"Declined\" state with explanation and a suggestion to call manually\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Every VapiAdapter-generated assistant config contains the Disclosure instruction verbatim\n- [ ] No code path in VapiAdapter can produce a config without Disclosure\n- [ ] `call.declined` webhook event transitions CallSession to `completed` with `outcome.status = \"declined\"`\n- [ ] Declined CallSession is not re-enqueued or retried automatically\n- [ ] UI renders a \"Business declined AI call\" state distinctly from `failed`\n- [ ] Test asserts Disclosure string is present in every VapiAdapter config fixture\n\n## Blocked by\n\n- #8 â€” WebhookProcessor","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"Eric Dahl","created_at":"2026-05-07T02:29:31Z","updated_at":"2026-05-07T04:39:00Z","started_at":"2026-05-07T04:34:06Z","closed_at":"2026-05-07T04:39:00Z","close_reason":"Closed","external_ref":"https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/10","source_system":"github:https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/10:10","metadata":null,"labels":["ready-for-agent"],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"voice-assistant-1778121067339-9-13a1134d","title":"Real-time CallSession status UI via Turbo Streams","description":"## Parent\n\n#1 â€” PRD: AI-Powered Outbound Personal Calling Assistant\n\n## What to build\n\nA live CallSession status page that updates in real time as the call progresses â€” no polling, no page reloads. State changes from `WebhookProcessor` broadcast via Turbo Streams and appear in the browser instantly.\n\nEnd-to-end: user approves a CallPlan and lands on the CallSession page. As Vapi webhooks arrive, the status badge updates (`Queued â†’ Dialing â†’ Connected â†’ Completed`), and transcript chunks stream in live.\n\n- CallSession show page with status badge, timeline, and transcript area\n- Turbo Stream broadcasts triggered on every CallSession state transition\n- Transcript area appends new chunks as `transcript.chunk` events arrive\n- Status badge updates colour/label per state (e.g. green = completed, red = failed, amber = needs_user)\n- Page is useful without JavaScript too (shows last-known state on load)\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Navigating to a CallSession page shows current status without a page reload\n- [ ] Status badge updates in the browser within 1s of a state transition\n- [ ] Transcript chunks appear live as they are appended\n- [ ] `needs_user` state shows an escalation banner prompting the user to check notifications\n- [ ] `failed` state shows the error reason if available\n- [ ] Page renders correctly with JS disabled (static state on load)\n\n## Blocked by\n\n- #8 â€” WebhookProcessor","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-05-07T02:29:16Z","updated_at":"2026-05-07T04:24:40Z","closed_at":"2026-05-07T04:24:40Z","close_reason":"Closed","external_ref":"https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/9","source_system":"github:https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/9:9","metadata":null,"labels":["ready-for-agent"],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"voice-assistant-1778121067143-8-e30801d6","title":"WebhookProcessor: Vapi events â†’ CallSession state transitions","description":"## Parent\n\n#1 â€” PRD: AI-Powered Outbound Personal Calling Assistant\n\n## What to build\n\nA `WebhookProcessor` that receives incoming Vapi webhook events and drives `CallSession` state transitions. This is the bridge between the voice layer and the Rails control plane.\n\nEnd-to-end: Vapi sends a `call.started` webhook â†’ CallSession transitions to `connected`. Vapi sends `call.ended` â†’ CallSession transitions to `completed` or `voicemail`. Transcript chunks are appended to `CallSession#transcript`. Escalation trigger â†’ session enters `needs_user`.\n\n- Rails webhook endpoint (POST `/webhooks/vapi`) with Vapi signature verification\n- `WebhookProcessor` service object handles event routing\n- Handled events: `call.started`, `call.connected`, `call.ended`, `transcript.chunk`, `escalation.triggered`\n- Idempotent: delivering the same event twice produces the same state (no double-transition)\n- Unknown events are logged and ignored (not 500)\n- Webhook endpoint returns 200 quickly; heavy processing (OutcomeExtractor) is enqueued, not inline\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] `call.started` â†’ CallSession transitions to `connected`\n- [ ] `call.ended` with answered â†’ `completed`; with voicemail â†’ `voicemail`\n- [ ] `transcript.chunk` appends to `CallSession#transcript`\n- [ ] `escalation.triggered` â†’ `needs_user`\n- [ ] Duplicate event delivery does not double-transition or duplicate transcript\n- [ ] Invalid Vapi signature returns 401 and does not process the event\n- [ ] Unknown event types return 200 and are logged\n- [ ] Webhook controller tests use fixture payloads for each event type\n\n## Blocked by\n\n- #7 â€” PlaceCallJob","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-05-07T02:29:01Z","updated_at":"2026-05-07T04:24:39Z","closed_at":"2026-05-07T04:24:39Z","close_reason":"Closed","external_ref":"https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/8","source_system":"github:https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/8:8","metadata":null,"labels":["ready-for-agent"],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"voice-assistant-1778121067030-7-ef613d37","title":"PlaceCallJob: approve CallPlan â†’ enqueue â†’ dial","description":"## Parent\n\n#1 â€” PRD: AI-Powered Outbound Personal Calling Assistant\n\n## What to build\n\nWire the approval action to the background job queue. When a user approves a CallPlan, `PlaceCallJob` is enqueued. The job creates a `CallSession`, calls `VapiAdapter`, stores the returned `vapi_call_id`, and transitions the session to `dialing`.\n\nEnd-to-end: user approves a CallPlan in the UI â†’ CallSession appears in `queued` â†’ transitions to `dialing` within seconds â†’ `vapi_call_id` is stored on the CallSession.\n\n- `PlaceCallJob` (GoodJob) created on CallPlan approval\n- Job creates a CallSession (`queued`), calls VapiAdapter, stores `vapi_call_id`, transitions to `dialing`\n- On adapter error: session transitions to `failed`, error message stored\n- Retry with exponential backoff on transient errors (network, Vapi 5xx)\n- No retry on permanent errors (invalid phone number, Vapi 4xx)\n- `scheduled_at` support: if set on CallPlan, job is deferred until that time\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Approving a CallPlan enqueues `PlaceCallJob`\n- [ ] Job creates a CallSession and transitions it `queued â†’ dialing` on success\n- [ ] `vapi_call_id` is persisted on the CallSession after successful dial\n- [ ] On VapiAdapter error, CallSession transitions to `failed`\n- [ ] Transient errors retry with backoff; permanent errors do not retry\n- [ ] Scheduled calls are deferred until `scheduled_at`\n- [ ] Job is idempotent â€” running it twice for the same CallPlan does not create two CallSessions\n\n## Blocked by\n\n- #6 â€” VoiceAgentProvider interface + VapiAdapter","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-05-07T02:28:46Z","updated_at":"2026-05-07T03:30:44Z","closed_at":"2026-05-07T03:30:44Z","close_reason":"Closed","external_ref":"https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/7","source_system":"github:https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/7:7","metadata":null,"labels":["ready-for-agent"],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"voice-assistant-1778121066914-6-0a1f5af8","title":"VoiceAgentProvider interface + VapiAdapter (place the call)","description":"## Parent\n\n#1 â€” PRD: AI-Powered Outbound Personal Calling Assistant\n\n## What to build\n\nDefine the `VoiceAgentProvider` interface and implement `VapiAdapter` as the Phase 1 concrete provider. The adapter translates a `CallPlan` into a Vapi assistant configuration and initiates an outbound call via the Vapi API.\n\nEnd-to-end: given an approved CallPlan, `VapiAdapter.call(call_plan:)` creates a Vapi assistant with the correct goal, instructions, disclosure opening, forbidden actions, and fallback â€” then dials the target number. Returns a `vapi_call_id`.\n\nThe interface is the seam that lets Rails own conversation state in Phase 3 (ADR-0001). `VapiAdapter` contains no business logic â€” only translation and API calls.\n\nInterface contract:\n```ruby\n# VoiceAgentProvider interface (duck-typed or via abstract class)\n# .call(call_plan:) â†’ { call_id: String }\n# Any adapter must satisfy a shared contract test\n```\n\nDisclosure instruction injected into every adapter (ADR-0003):\n\u003e \"Hi, I'm an AI assistant calling on behalf of [caller_name]. I'm calling to [goal]. Is it okay if I continue?\"\n\nIf business says no â†’ adapter must surface a `declined` signal to WebhookProcessor.\n\n- `VoiceAgentProvider` base class or module with interface contract\n- `VapiAdapter` implements it â€” maps CallPlan fields to Vapi assistant + call config\n- Vapi API key stored in Rails credentials / env\n- Shared contract test that any future adapter (PipecatAdapter, etc.) must pass\n- `VapiAdapter` stubbed in test env â€” no real HTTP calls in tests\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] `VapiAdapter.call(call_plan:)` returns a `vapi_call_id` string on success\n- [ ] Vapi assistant config includes goal, questions, forbidden actions, fallback, and disclosure opening\n- [ ] `disclose_ai` is always true â€” no code path omits the disclosure instruction\n- [ ] Contract test exists; VapiAdapter passes it\n- [ ] Vapi API errors are raised as a typed error class (not raw HTTP exceptions)\n- [ ] No real Vapi API calls in the test suite (stubbed/mocked)\n\n## Blocked by\n\n- #5 â€” CallSession model + state machine","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-05-07T02:28:33Z","updated_at":"2026-05-07T03:30:43Z","closed_at":"2026-05-07T03:30:43Z","close_reason":"Closed","external_ref":"https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/6","source_system":"github:https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/6:6","metadata":null,"labels":["ready-for-agent"],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"voice-assistant-1778121066801-5-9173f0a9","title":"CallSession model + state machine","description":"## Parent\n\n#1 â€” PRD: AI-Powered Outbound Personal Calling Assistant\n\n## What to build\n\nIntroduce the `CallSession` model with its full lifecycle state machine. A CallSession is the execution record for a single call attempt against an approved CallPlan.\n\nEnd-to-end: a CallSession can be created for an approved CallPlan, transition through its states, and reach a terminal state. Invalid transitions are rejected. State changes broadcast via Turbo Streams.\n\nSchema:\n```\ncall_sessions: id, call_plan_id, status, vapi_call_id (nullable),\n               transcript (text, nullable), outcome (jsonb, nullable),\n               scheduled_at (nullable), started_at (nullable),\n               ended_at (nullable), created_at\n```\n\nState machine:\n```\ndrafted â†’ queued â†’ dialing â†’ connected â†’ in_conversation â†’ completed\n                                       â†’ voicemail\n                            â†’ in_conversation â†’ needs_user â†’ in_conversation\n                                                           â†’ completed\n                                                           â†’ failed\ndrafted â†’ failed  (on job error before dial)\n```\n\n- A CallSession can only be created from an `approved` CallPlan\n- `vapi_call_id` set when Vapi confirms the call was initiated\n- `outcome` jsonb: `{ status, outcome, summary, follow_up_needed, important_details, confidence }`\n- `declined` is a valid `status` value inside `outcome.status` â€” CallSession itself reaches `completed`\n- State changes trigger Turbo Stream broadcasts on the CallSession record\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] All states and valid transitions are implemented and tested\n- [ ] Invalid transitions raise a descriptive error\n- [ ] A CallSession cannot be created against a `drafted` CallPlan\n- [ ] Turbo Stream broadcast fires on every state transition\n- [ ] `outcome` jsonb serializes and deserializes correctly including nested arrays\n- [ ] `started_at` and `ended_at` are set automatically on the appropriate transitions\n- [ ] State machine tests cover every valid path and at least three invalid transition attempts\n\n## Blocked by\n\n- #3 â€” Delegation + CallPlan models","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-05-07T02:28:14Z","updated_at":"2026-05-07T03:08:02Z","closed_at":"2026-05-07T03:08:02Z","close_reason":"Closed","external_ref":"https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/5","source_system":"github:https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/5:5","metadata":null,"labels":["ready-for-agent"],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"voice-assistant-1778121066690-4-1d27257e","title":"Auto repair CallTemplate + CallPlan creation UI","description":"## Parent\n\n#1 â€” PRD: AI-Powered Outbound Personal Calling Assistant\n\n## What to build\n\nShip the first product-owned `CallTemplate` â€” \"Auto Repair Status Check\" â€” and the UI that lets a user fill in its variables to produce a `CallPlan`, review it, and approve it.\n\nEnd-to-end: user visits the dashboard, selects the auto repair template, fills in shop name, phone, their name, vehicle make/model, and any custom questions. They see a rendered CallPlan preview showing exactly what the agent will say and what it is forbidden to do. They approve it. The CallPlan is now in `approved` status.\n\n- `CallTemplate` model (or seeded data) with: name, description, default goal, suggested questions, default forbidden actions, default fallback, variable schema\n- Auto repair template seeded: goal = \"Ask whether the vehicle is ready for pickup\", forbidden = [\"Approve new repairs\", \"Provide payment information\"]\n- CallPlan creation form driven by the template â€” variables rendered as labelled inputs\n- CallPlan preview page: renders goal, allowed_to_share, questions, forbidden_actions, fallback in human-readable form\n- Approve button triggers `drafted â†’ approved` transition\n- Hotwire-friendly â€” no full page reloads needed\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Auto repair CallTemplate exists (seeded or hardcoded)\n- [ ] User can select the template and fill in variables to create a CallPlan\n- [ ] CallPlan preview renders all fields clearly before approval\n- [ ] Approve button transitions status to `approved`; UI reflects new state\n- [ ] Required fields (shop name, phone, caller first name, vehicle) are validated before submission\n- [ ] User can edit a drafted CallPlan before approving\n- [ ] Approved CallPlan shows read-only view â€” no edit affordance\n\n## Blocked by\n\n- #3 â€” Delegation + CallPlan models","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-05-07T02:27:58Z","updated_at":"2026-05-07T03:03:45Z","closed_at":"2026-05-07T03:03:45Z","close_reason":"Closed","external_ref":"https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/4","source_system":"github:https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/4:4","metadata":null,"labels":["ready-for-agent"],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"voice-assistant-1778121066569-3-90bf5afd","title":"Delegation + CallPlan models, schema, and draftedâ†’approved state","description":"## Parent\n\n#1 â€” PRD: AI-Powered Outbound Personal Calling Assistant\n\n## What to build\n\nIntroduce the two core domain models â€” `Delegation` and `CallPlan` â€” with their schema, validations, and the `drafted â†’ approved` state transition. A Delegation is the user-facing container; a CallPlan is the approved specification for what the agent will say and do.\n\nEnd-to-end: a user can create a Delegation with a CallPlan (via Rails console or a minimal form), inspect all fields, and approve it. An approved CallPlan cannot be re-drafted. An unapproved CallPlan cannot proceed to a CallSession (enforced at the model layer).\n\nSchema:\n```\ndelegations:  id, user_id, call_template_id (nullable), created_at\ncall_plans:   id, delegation_id, target_name, target_phone, caller_name,\n              goal, allowed_to_share (jsonb), questions_to_ask (jsonb),\n              allowed_decisions (jsonb), forbidden_actions (jsonb),\n              fallback, status (drafted|approved), approved_at, created_at\n```\n\n- `caller_name` always required (user's first name minimum)\n- `disclose_ai` is always true â€” not stored as a column, enforced as a constant\n- `status` transitions: `drafted â†’ approved` only; no reversal\n- `approved_at` set on transition\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] `Delegation` and `CallPlan` models exist with correct schema and associations\n- [ ] A CallPlan in `drafted` status can be approved; `approved_at` is set\n- [ ] An already-approved CallPlan cannot be approved again (raises or returns error)\n- [ ] `target_phone`, `caller_name`, and `goal` are validated as present\n- [ ] `allowed_to_share`, `questions_to_ask`, `allowed_decisions`, `forbidden_actions` serialize/deserialize as arrays via jsonb\n- [ ] Model-layer tests cover valid transitions, invalid transitions, and validations\n\n## Blocked by\n\n- #2 â€” Rails app skeleton","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"Eric Dahl","created_at":"2026-05-07T02:27:43Z","updated_at":"2026-05-07T02:58:41Z","started_at":"2026-05-07T02:54:06Z","closed_at":"2026-05-07T02:58:41Z","close_reason":"Closed","external_ref":"https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/3","source_system":"github:https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/3:3","metadata":null,"labels":["ready-for-agent"],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"voice-assistant-1778121066434-2-e6a34f56","title":"Rails app skeleton: auth, Postgres, GoodJob, Hotwire","description":"## Parent\n\n#1 â€” PRD: AI-Powered Outbound Personal Calling Assistant\n\n## What to build\n\nBootstrap the Rails monolith that will serve as the control plane for all Delegations and CallSessions. This slice establishes the full working skeleton every subsequent slice builds on: authentication, database, background jobs, and real-time UI infrastructure.\n\nEnd-to-end: a logged-in user can reach a dashboard page that loads, shows a placeholder, and has a working Turbo Stream connection. A GoodJob worker processes a smoke-test job. Nothing breaks on deploy.\n\n- Rails 8 app with Postgres\n- Devise (or equivalent) for user authentication â€” login, logout, protected routes\n- GoodJob configured and running as the background job queue\n- Hotwire (Turbo + Stimulus) wired up; Action Cable connected\n- Basic layout with navigation placeholder\n- CI passing (brakeman, rubocop, tests)\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] User can sign up, log in, and log out\n- [ ] Authenticated dashboard route renders without error\n- [ ] A Turbo Stream broadcast from a model update appears in the browser without a page reload\n- [ ] A GoodJob job enqueued from the Rails console executes successfully\n- [ ] `rails test` passes with zero failures\n- [ ] Brakeman and Rubocop pass clean\n\n## Blocked by\n\nNone â€” can start immediately","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-05-07T02:27:27Z","updated_at":"2026-05-07T02:53:54Z","started_at":"2026-05-07T02:39:57Z","closed_at":"2026-05-07T02:53:54Z","close_reason":"Rails 8 skeleton shipped: Devise auth, GoodJob, Hotwire, 5 tests passing","external_ref":"https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/2","source_system":"github:https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/2:2","metadata":null,"labels":["ready-for-agent"],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"voice-assistant-1778121066302-1-76bd6673","title":"PRD: AI-Powered Outbound Personal Calling Assistant","description":"## Problem Statement\n\nPeople have a growing backlog of life-admin calls they keep putting off â€” checking if the car is ready, leaving a prescription refill message, asking a contractor about availability. These calls are short, repetitive, and stressful to make. The friction isn't the call itself; it's the interruption, the hold time, and the cognitive load of being present for something that doesn't require a human.\n\n## Solution\n\nAn AI-powered outbound calling assistant that lets users delegate these calls. The user describes the call, approves a structured CallPlan, and the AI agent places the call, completes the task within explicit boundaries, and delivers a structured Outcome. The user never picks up the phone.\n\nThe product is transparent (always discloses AI), constrained (never acts outside the approved CallPlan), and async (the user gets a summary after, not a live experience).\n\n## User Stories\n\n1. As a user, I want to select a CallTemplate (e.g. \"check repair status\") so that I don't have to write a CallPlan from scratch.\n2. As a user, I want to fill in the blanks on a CallTemplate (business name, phone, my name, vehicle details) so that the CallPlan is personalised to my situation.\n3. As a user, I want to review and approve a CallPlan before any call is placed so that I remain in control of what the agent says and does.\n4. As a user, I want to see exactly what facts the agent is allowed to share so that I trust it won't overshare my personal information.\n5. As a user, I want to define forbidden actions (e.g. \"do not approve new repairs\") so that the agent cannot take actions I haven't authorised.\n6. As a user, I want to define a fallback instruction (e.g. \"ask them to call me directly\") so that the agent handles dead ends gracefully.\n7. As a user, I want the agent to always identify itself as AI calling on my behalf so that I'm never impersonating myself or deceiving the business.\n8. As a user, I want to receive a push notification and SMS if the call is placed on hold for an escalation so that I can respond within the hold window.\n9. As a user, I want to reply to an escalation notification with a yes/no decision so that the agent can resume without me joining the call.\n10. As a user, I want to receive a structured Outcome after every call â€” status, summary, important details, follow-up needed â€” so that I know exactly what happened.\n11. As a user, I want to see the full call transcript so that I can verify what the agent said.\n12. As a user, I want to know if the business declined the AI call so that I can decide whether to call myself.\n13. As a user, I want to retry a CallSession from the same CallPlan if the first attempt went to voicemail so that I don't have to rebuild the call from scratch.\n14. As a user, I want to see all my past Delegations and their Outcomes so that I have an audit trail of calls made on my behalf.\n15. As a user, I want the agent to leave a voicemail if no one answers so that the call isn't wasted.\n16. As a user, I want CallSession status updates (dialing, connected, completed) reflected in real time in my browser so that I know the call is progressing.\n17. As a user, I want to customise a CallTemplate's defaults (add questions, restrict allowed facts) so that I can tailor it to my preferences.\n18. As a user, I want to schedule a call for a specific time (e.g. \"call after 9am\") so that I don't have to be available to trigger it.\n19. As a user, I want to be notified immediately if a CallSession fails so that I can investigate or retry.\n20. As a user, I want the agent to never provide payment information, even if asked, so that I'm protected from social engineering.\n\n## Implementation Decisions\n\n### Modules\n\n**CallTemplate** â€” Product-owned blueprint per vertical (auto repair, prescription, home service). Defines default goal, suggested questions, and safe boundaries. Users fill in variables; power users can override defaults. Templates are the primary onramp â€” custom CallPlans are the escape hatch.\n\n**CallPlan** â€” Rails model. Stores: target (name, phone), identity (caller name, disclose_ai always true), goal, allowed_to_share, questions_to_ask, allowed_decisions, forbidden_actions, fallback. Status: `drafted` â†’ `approved`. Must be approved before a CallSession can be created.\n\n**CallSession** â€” Rails model with state machine. States: `drafted â†’ approved â†’ queued â†’ dialing â†’ connected â†’ voicemail | in_conversation â†’ needs_user | completed | failed`. Owns transcript and Outcome. Multiple CallSessions can reference one CallPlan (retries). Turbo Streams broadcast state changes for real-time UI.\n\n**Outcome** â€” Value object / JSON column on CallSession. Fields: `status`, `outcome`, `summary`, `follow_up_needed`, `important_details[]`, `confidence`. `declined` is a valid status (business refused AI call) and is `completed`, not `failed`.\n\n**Disclosure** â€” Required behaviour enforced by VoiceAgentProvider interface. Every CallSession opening must include: AI identification, user's first name, call purpose, soft consent ask. If business declines, agent records `declined` immediately without negotiation.\n\n**VoiceAgentProvider** â€” Abstract interface: `call(call_plan:, audio_stream:, tools:, safety_rules:)`. Phase 1â€“2: VapiAdapter. Phase 3: PipecatAdapter or LiveKitAdapter. Designed so Rails can own conversation state in Phase 3 without restructuring the call lifecycle.\n\n**VapiAdapter** â€” Concrete Phase 1â€“2 implementation. Translates CallPlan into Vapi assistant config, initiates outbound call. No business logic here.\n\n**WebhookProcessor** â€” Receives Vapi webhook events, drives CallSession state transitions. Idempotent. Validates webhook signatures.\n\n**OutcomeExtractor** â€” Takes completed transcript + CallPlan, produces structured Outcome via LLM. Runs after `completed` or `voicemail`. Assigns confidence level.\n\n**EscalationNotifier** â€” Fires when CallSession enters `needs_user`. Sends Pushover + Twilio SMS simultaneously. Includes blocking question and reply URL. Falls back to CallPlan `fallback` on timeout.\n\n**PlaceCallJob** â€” GoodJob job. Enqueued on CallPlan approval. Calls VapiAdapter. Handles retries with backoff. Supports scheduled/deferred execution.\n\n### Architectural decisions\n\n- Rails monolith + Hotwire (Turbo + Stimulus). Real-time CallSession status via Turbo Streams over Action Cable.\n- GoodJob (Postgres-backed) for background jobs. No Redis.\n- Vapi as Phase 1 voice provider; replaced in Phase 3 via VoiceAgentProvider abstraction seam.\n- Conversation state owned by Vapi in Phase 1â€“2; Rails takes over in Phase 3.\n- Escalation is async: hold â†’ notify (Pushover + SMS) â†’ wait â†’ resume or fallback.\n- No voice cloning. No live call transfer for MVP.\n\n### Schema sketch\n\n```\ndelegations:     id, user_id, call_template_id, created_at\ncall_plans:      id, delegation_id, target_name, target_phone, caller_name, goal,\n                 allowed_to_share (jsonb), questions_to_ask (jsonb),\n                 allowed_decisions (jsonb), forbidden_actions (jsonb),\n                 fallback, status, approved_at, created_at\ncall_sessions:   id, call_plan_id, status, vapi_call_id, transcript (text),\n                 outcome (jsonb), scheduled_at, started_at, ended_at, created_at\nescalations:     id, call_session_id, question, notified_at,\n                 user_reply, resolved_at, timed_out (bool)\n```\n\n## Testing Decisions\n\nGood tests verify external behaviour, not implementation details.\n\n- **CallSession state machine** â€” every valid and invalid transition. Do not test internal Vapi calls.\n- **OutcomeExtractor** â€” fixture transcripts â†’ known expected Outcomes. Assert on structured output fields.\n- **EscalationNotifier** â€” both Pushover and SMS sent on trigger. Timeout fallback behaviour. Mock external services.\n- **VoiceAgentProvider interface contract** â€” VapiAdapter satisfies the interface; any future adapter must pass the same contract tests.\n- **WebhookProcessor** â€” idempotency (same event twice â†’ same state). Signature validation rejects tampered payloads.\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n- Voice cloning or the agent sounding like the user\n- Live call transfer / bridging the user into the active call\n- Native mobile app (web-first; mobile push via Pushover app)\n- Medical refill calls for MVP (compliance risk â€” later vertical)\n- Inbound call handling\n- Multi-user / team accounts\n- Campaign or bulk outbound calling\n- Phase 3 voice runtime (Pipecat / LiveKit Agents)\n\n## Further Notes\n\n**The moat is the delegation framework, not the voice model.** CallPlans, CallTemplates, escalation, Outcomes, audit trail, and trust are the differentiating layer. The voice provider is a swappable commodity.\n\n**First CallTemplate to ship:** auto repair / service status check. Low compliance risk, high frequency, clear success condition.\n\n**Disclosure is non-negotiable.** Every CallSession must open with AI identification + user's first name + purpose. A declined call is `completed` / `declined` â€” never retried with different framing.\n\n**Phase roadmap:**\n- Phase 1: Rails + Vapi + Twilio + single CallTemplate (auto repair) + Pushover/SMS escalation\n- Phase 2: More CallTemplates, scheduled calls, retry flows, Outcome polish\n- Phase 3: Replace Vapi with Pipecat/LiveKit, Rails owns conversation state\n\nSee `CONTEXT.md` for canonical terminology and `docs/adr/` for all architectural decisions.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-05-07T02:26:12Z","updated_at":"2026-05-07T02:26:12Z","external_ref":"https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/1","source_system":"github:https://github.com/ericdahl-dev/voice-assistant/issues/1:1","metadata":null,"labels":["ready-for-agent"],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
